Jatri API Documentation

Documentation Version 2.0

getting started get all cities get trips get seat plan Ticket pending block Ticket Purchase Ticket Cancel Ticket Status Ticket Search

Introduction

Item Name : Jatri ticket search, booking and purchased system

Item Version : v 2.0

Author : Jatri Devs

First of all, Thank you so much for using our API.

This documentation is to help you to regard each step of customization. Please go through the documentation carefully to understand how this works. API documentation is arranged in order by which they will need to be called.

Getting Started

Step 01) Get Access token

Url : {baseUrl}/login
Method/Action Type : Form POST
Return Response : json format
NOTE : The access token will be available/worked for the next 24 hours once it is created

Body / Params

Param name Type Description Required
username String your secret username Yes
password String your secret password Yes

Sample Request Payload 

                                        
                                            curl --location '{{baseUrl}}/login' \
                                            --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
                                            --data '{
                                                "username": "your_secret_username",
                                                "password": "your_secret_password"
                                            }'

Sample Response Payload 

                                      
                                        {
                                            "status": "SUCCESS",
                                            "accessToken": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9....",
                                            "expDateTime": "2024-03-16T16:00:00.580Z"
                                        }

Error Responses

Status Code Type Message Path Method Timestamp
401 UNAUTHORIZED Invalid username/password for DT TP! /login POST 2024-02-05T05:31:42.704Z

Get all cities

Step 02) Get all cities

Url : {{baseUrl}}/v2/cities
Method/Action Type : Form GET
Return Response : json format
NOTE :

Headers

Param name Type Description Required
Authorization String Bearer {{accessToken}}
accessToken can be retrieved by calling 'Get Access Token’ api 		Yes

Sample Request Payload 

                                      
                                        curl --location '{{baseUrl}}/v2/cities' \
                                        --header 'Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}'

Sample Response Payload 

                                      
                                          {
                                              "status": "SUCCESS",
                                              "cities": [
                                                  "Bagerhat",
                                                  "Bandarban",
                                                  "Banglabandha",
                                                  "Barguna",
                                                  "Barisal",
                                                  "Benapole",
                                                  "Chattogram",
                                                  "Comilla",
                                                  "Cox's Bazar",
                                                  "Dangmorka",
                                                  "Dhaka",

                                                  "Feni",

                                                  "Gazipur",
                                                  "Gopalganj",
                                                  "Habiganj",

                                              ]
                                          }

Get trips

Step 03) Get trips

Url : {{baseUrl}}/v2/trip/search-trips
Method/Action Type : Form GET
Return Response : json format
NOTE :

Headers

Param name Type Description Required
Authorization String Bearer {{accessToken}} Yes

Body / Params

Param name Type Description Required
from String From city name Yes
to String To city name Yes
busType String [AC, NON_AC, ALL] ALL Yes
date String [YYYY-MM-DD] Date must be greater than today Yes

Sample Request Payload 

                                      
                                        curl --location '{{baseUrl}}/v2/trip/search-trips?from=Dhaka&to=Cox%27s%20Bazar&busType=ALL&date=2024-02-05' \
                                        --header 'Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}'

Get seat plan

Step 04) Get seat plan

Url : {{baseUrl}}/v2/trip/seat-plan
Method/Action Type : Form GET
Return Response : json format
NOTE :

Headers

Param name Type Description Required
Authorization String Bearer {{accessToken}} Yes

Body / Params

Param name Type Description Required
from String From city name Yes
to String To city name Yes
trip String Trip id of a particular trip
"trip" can be retrieved by calling "Get Trips" api 		Yes

Sample Request Payload 

                                        
                                          curl --location '{{baseUrl}}/v2/trip/seat-plan/?from=Dhaka&to=Cox%27s%20Bazar&trip=65bbfb897b5d1277d194fc44' \
                                          --header 'Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}'

ticket pending block

Step 05) ticket pending block

Url : {{baseUrl}}/v2/ticket-pending-block
Method/Action Type : Form POST
Return Response : json format
NOTE :

Headers

Param name Type Description Required
Authorization String Bearer {{accessToken}} Yes

Body / Params

Param name Type Description Required
trip String Trip id Yes
from String From city name Yes
to String To city name Yes
boardingPlace String Passenger's boarding point
"counter._id" from boarding object in fares array can be retrieved by calling "Get Seat Plan" api 		Yes
droppingPoint String Passenger's dropping point
"counter._id" from dropping object in fares array can be retrieved by calling "Get Seat Plan" api 		Yes
sid String An unique id for each object in fares array
"sid" from object in fares array can be retrieved by calling "Get Seat Plan" api 		Yes
oid string "oid" from object in fares array can be retrieved by calling "Get Seat Plan" api Yes
seatFare Number Total fare Yes
farePerSeat Array Seat no. and the fare of that seat Yes
passengerName String Passenger's name Yes
passengerPhone String Passenger's phone number Yes
passengerEmail String Passenger's email Yes
passengerGender String [MALE, FEMALE, OTHER] Passenger's gender Yes
passengerNid String Passenger's nid No

Sample Request Payload 

                                        
                                          curl --location '{{baseUrl}}/v2/ticket-pending-block' \
                                          --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
                                          --header 'Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}' \
                                          --data-raw '{
                                              "trip": "65bbfb897b5d1277d194fc44",
                                              "boardingPlace": "6475c6c017127bad97c2b835",
                                              "droppingPoint": "6475cae6907cdb463e51d590",
                                              "sid": "65bbfb897b5d1277d194fc51",
                                              "oid": null,
                                              "seatFare": 3000,
                                              "farePerSeat": [
                                                  {
                                                      "seat": "A3",
                                                      "fare": 1500
                                                  },
                                                  {
                                                      "seat": "A4",
                                                      "fare": 1500
                                                  }
                                              ],
                                              "passengerName": "Prince Vegeta",
                                              "passengerPhone": "01842626668",
                                              "passengerEmail": "vegeta@saiyaan.com",
                                              "passengerAddress": "Earth",
                                              "passengerGender": "MALE"
                                          }'

Sample Response Payload 

                                        
                                            {
                                                "status": "SUCCESS",
                                                "dtId": "65bf629bf23b0e523e548ff1"
                                            }

Error Responses

Status Code Type Message Path Method Timestamp
400 SEAT_ON_PROGRESS Seat/s already in progress /v2/ticket-pending-block POST 2024-02-05T06:05:02.336Z
400 INVALID_COUNTER Invalid Counter /v2/ticket-pending-block POST 2024-02-05T06:08:09.304Z
400 INVALID_TRIP_INFORMATION Invalid Trip Information /v2/ticket-pending-block POST 2024-02-05T06:08:09.304Z
400 INVALID_FARE Invalid fare for this trip! /v2/ticket-pending-block POST 2024-02-05T06:08:09.304Z
400 BAD_REQUEST Invalid fare calculation: invalid fare per seat /v2/ticket-pending-block POST 2024-02-05T06:08:09.304Z
400 BAD_REQUEST Seat A3,A4 already sold/reserved! /v2/ticket-pending-block POST 2024-02-05T06:08:09.304Z
